Sure, here are five example sentences in Serbian that use the word "sloboda" in different forms and positions:

1. *Sloboda* je osnovno pravo svakog čoveka. (Freedom is a basic right of every human being.)
2. Oni su se borili za *slobodu* svoje zemlje. (They fought for the freedom of their country.)
3. *Slobodan* sam večeras, hoćeš li izaći sa mnom? (I am free tonight, do you want to go out with me?)
4. Drago mi je da si se oslobodio svojih okova i pronašao *slobodu*. (I'm glad you broke free from your chains and found freedom.)
5. U ovoj zemlji ima *slobode* govora i izražavanja. (In this country, there is freedom of speech and expression.)

I hope this helps!